Nantucket Cranberry Pie
 - Sue Hubbell

3 c fresh cranberries
sugar to coat the berries
1/2 c chopped walnuts
1 c flour
1 1/4 tsp baking powder
1/8 tsp salt
1/4 c shortening
1 c sugar
1 egg
1/3 c milk
1/2 tsp vanilla
1/8 tsp almond extract

Rinse cranberries and dredge with sugar. Pour into greased 10" pie tin, leaving excess sugar in bowl. Add chopped walnuts to cranberries. Cream shortneing with 1 c sugar. Add dry ingredients alternately with mixture of egg, milk, vanilla, and almond. Spoon and spread over cranberries and walnuts. Bake at 350F for 25-30 min.
